      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">19.309</ph> Solicitation provisions
and contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1151e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e15">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        Insert
the provision at <xref href="52.219-1.dita#FAR_52_219_1"
                              base="i1057235"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-1</xref>, Small
Business Program Representations, in solicitations exceeding the micro-purchase
threshold when the contract is for supplies to be delivered or services
to be performed in the United States or its outlying areas, or when
the contracting officer has applied this part in accordance with <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(b)(1)(ii).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e31">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Use the
provision with its Alternate I in solicitations issued by DoD, NASA,
or the Coast Guard.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e36">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Use the provision with its Alternate II in solicitations that will result in a multiple-award contract with more than one NAICS code assigned. This is authorized for solicitations issued after October 1, 2028 (see <xref href="19.102.dita#FAR_19_102"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(b)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e44">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  When contracting by sealed
bidding, insert the provision at <xref href="52.219-2.dita#FAR_52_219_2"
                        base="i1057302"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-2</xref>, Equal Low Bids,
in solicitations when the contract is for supplies to be delivered
or services to be performed in the United States or its outlying
areas, or when the contracting officer has applied this part in
accordance with <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(b)(1)(ii).
               </p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e60">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e65">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-28.dita#FAR_52_219_28"
                              base="i1057874"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-28</xref>, <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2020-016?>Postaward<?FM MARKER [Why] 8. Amend section 19.309 in paragraph (c)(1) by removing “Post-Award” and adding “Postaward” in its place.?></ph> Small Business Program Rerepresentation, in solicitations and contracts exceeding the micro-purchase threshold when the contract is for supplies to be delivered or services to be performed in the United States or its outlying areas, or when the contracting officer has applied this part in accordance with <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(b)(1)(ii). </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1180e81">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Use the clause with its Alternate I in solicitations and the resulting multiple-award contracts with more than one NAICS code. This is authorized for solicitations issued after October 1, 2028 (see <xref href="19.102.dita#FAR_19_102"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(b)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
